# ============================================
# OPTIONAL: Specific to your workflow
# ============================================

# Uncomment if using:
# database dumps
# *.sql
# *.db

# Large files
# *.zip
# *.tar.gz
# *.rar

# Media files (if not needed in repo)
# *.mp4
# *.mov
# *.mp3
# *.wav

# ============================================
# SECURITY: CRITICAL FILES
# ============================================

# NEVER commit:
*.key
*.pem
*.pfx
*.p12
private-key*
secret*
.credentials
.aws/
.ssh/
.gnupg/

# ============================================
# ALLOWLIST (opposite of ignore)
# ============================================

# Exception: DO commit these files
# (Use ! to negate ignore rules)
!.env.example
!.gitkeep
!.github/
!.github/workflows/
!.husky/
!public/
!src/
!tests/

# ============================================
# COMMENTS
# ============================================

# This .gitignore file ensures that:
# 1. Sensitive data (API keys, .env) never gets committed
# 2. Large generated files aren't tracked
# 3. Local development files stay private
# 4. Dependencies are managed through package.json
# 5. Build artifacts aren't versioned
#
# IMPORTANT REMINDERS:
# - .env must ALWAYS be ignored
# - API keys should never be in Git
# - Use .env.example as template instead
# - Review before committing with: git status
# - Use git secrets or pre-commit hooks to prevent accidents
